                    <h2>Agent-Based Modelling, Theory, Data</h2>
                    <!--<img class="right" src="../figures/burglar_behaviour-geotime.jpg"/> -->
                    
                    <p><i>Natural description:</i> Easy to incorporate social/behavioural theory</p>
                    <p><strong>BUT:</strong> Need detailed, high-resolution, individual-level data</p>
                    <blockquote>Advantages of model complexity and flexibility are tempered by the difficulties in finding suitable values for model parameters based on empirical evidence. </blockquote>
                    <p>'Big' data can help (?)</p>
                    
